 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uczectunare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Czec Tunare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/14/01 9:57:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Other Methods of Pulling</span><hr size=1> Hmmmm.... Don't know what happened to the rest of it.<br>
<br>
Forgive me if these have already been mentioned, I didn't have the patience to read EVERY post. I have stumbled upon a couple other methods of pulling i would like to share.<br>
<br>
&quot;Reverse&quot; Buff Pulling<br>
This is basically the opposite of Crouching Lizard's method of buff pulling. It works best in Velious (mobs that always go back right away) and requires pumice. If you want to pull a caster out of a group of melee's, simply dispell the caster using the pumice and feign when they reach you. Usually the melee's will go back leaving the caster rebuffing and ready to be pulled.<br>
<br>
Pulling Using a Low Level Mob<br>
This is a tactic I have not seen mentioned before, it works very well in some situations (namely in velious when mobs go back together). For this to work, there must be a low level mob, and the thing you want to pull must assist this mob. First, attack the low level mob, then bring it close to the group you wish to split. Slowly bring it closer and closer to the closest mob you want to pull. The mob closest to you will eventually agro (larger agro radius than if you didn't have something else attacking you) and come alone. The mob you are pulling is actually assisting the lower level mob you already have attacking you, while you are too far away for the others to assist. Sorry if this is not clear, I'm not very good at explaining some things.<br>
EXAMPLE: The place I use this tactic is Kael Drakkel, to pull mobs from the bank, king ramp, or arena. First, attack a dire wolf and make sure it is the only thing you have. Slowly Bring it close to the group you want to pull. As you inch closer, the front mob should attack you, leaving you with a big mob and a dire wolf which you can kill quickly.<br>
<br>
This obviously can't be used in many situations, as the low level mobs may be difficult to get to the area you wish to pull, or may be all together non existant. <br>
<br>
Czec<br>
57 Iksar Master <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ucalm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/01 7:42:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> something to add</span><hr size=1> I read through your list laotzu and I can think of specific times and places i would use ever single one of them.<br>
<br>
I have 2 more things i use in certain places only i'd like to add.<br>
<br>
CoH + invis pulling in chardok royals.  king and queen room, get with mage, call summon, pull, arrive and get invis and run back and tag what you want.  Great technique because many casters, none see invis, and chain puller isnt killed by AoE.<br>
<br>
Kael.  Things in kael run strait at you, yet get stuck in walls, you can use this to split the 3 protectors of zek at the arena. (all instant returners, all 3 aggro every time) but you can use the wall if you pull at angle.<br>
<br>
oh, plane of air.  Stuff will not path up islands (sat for 2 hours with bees aggroed and they wouldnt come up to drake island)<br>
<br>
above all, be creative.  If you are trying to get a particular spawn, the best way is not always brute force.  If invis works, if quarky pathing works, if sneak, or harmony, or dispell (for rebuff splitting), if something you make up on the spot works, use it.<br>
