sometimes you get 2 because another will buff the dispelled one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzenshiss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenshiss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/1/02 2:01:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sneak Yo</span><hr size=1> Well, obviously this hasn't been commented on in a while, but great list. Here's another technique I'd add:<br>
<br>
Blindness pulling: Get yourself a bioluminescent orb. Cast on one mob in the pack, let them aggro and run to you just a bit. FD immediately--the pack will return to bind spot, but the blindness on the mob you pulled will cause it to wander. Once all mobs have returned except your target, stand and wait for blindness to wear off. You have to be careful with this technique, because the blind pathing may be unexpected, but it's a great technique for splitting Kael arena giants.<br>
<br>
It's also the ONLY reliable technique I've ever used to pull Eashen solo away from his guards.<br>
